│  Numbered Steps:                                                            │
│  1. **Normalize the Text**: Convert the entire string to lowercase to       │
│  ensure case insensitivity.                                                 │
│  2. **Remove Non-Alphanumeric Characters**: Filter out all characters that  │
│  are not letters or digits. This involves iterating through the string and  │
│  constructing a new string with only alphanumeric characters.               │
│  3. **Check for Palindrome**: Compare the normalized string with its        │
│  reverse. If both are the same, return `True`; otherwise, return `False`.   │
│                                                                             │
│  Edge Cases:                                                                │
│  - An empty string (`""`) should return `True` since an empty string is     │
│  trivially a palindrome.                                                    │
│  - A string with only spaces (`"   "`) should return `True` because when    │
│  normalized, it becomes an empty string.                                    │
│  - A string that contains only punctuation marks (`"!!!"`) should return    │
│  `True`, as it also normalizes to an empty string.                          │
